    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but my doctor is always so rushed and i feel like they just follow a script. i've been keeping a very strict log of everything i eat and my activity levels are great, so i'm basically stable. if i were to just taper it down slowly, like 5mg to 3.5mg then to 2mg over a few weeks, would that be a safer way to manage it myself? it seems like a lot of unnecessary medication if my blood work has been fine for months.",
